      {
        "purpose": "english_translation",
        "value": "New-field high = 513,580.22 koku, marked 外二 ('additional, second'). Saga led the Edo period in intensive paddy reclamation across the Saga Plain; formal + new-field combined approaches 725k koku — far above the ~357k formal rating most secondary sources cite."
      },
